11... b6 12. Bd3 Ba6
{ This more direct move is also possible and even though it looks riskier, it is not easy to find a refutation, here are some possible lines. }
13. O-O { 13.Rc3  Bxd3  14.Qxd3  Nd7  15.O-O  transposes to the text move. }
13... Bxd3 14. Qxd3 Nd7 15. Rc3
{ White gains control over the c-file but as it turns out, he can't make use of it. }
15... Rc8 16. Rfc1 Rxc3 17. Qxc3 Nf6
{ Black is also fine, as the central pawn is under attack and Black can also follow with ...Qa8 and ...Rd8 or ...Rc8, depending on the circumstances. }
