19. Qc7
{ White tries to invade Black's position without trading queens, but here too, the rerouting of the knight solves Black's problems. }
19... Rd8 20. h4 Nf8
{ The already familiar knight maneuver, aiming for the d5-square, via g6-f4. }
21. h5 { White stops the knight from coming to g6. } 21... Rd7
{ Now Black kicks the queen out and prepares to play something like ...Qd8, ...Nh7-Ng5. }
22. Qc8 Qxc8 23. Rxc8 g6 24. g4 gxh5 25. gxh5 Kg7
{ Black is planning now ...Nh7-Ng5 when the knight problem will be solved so Black has nothing to fear here, the position is objectively equal. }
