17. h5 h6 18. Bb1 f5
{ Anticipating Qd3, Black has nothing to fear as the king can always escape via f8 if necessary now. }
19. exf6 Rxf6 20. Qd3 Rxf3 21. Qxf3 Qf6 22. Qe4 Rf8 23. Qh7+ Kf7
{ And the king on e7 is actually quite safe, only Black can be better here. } *

