19... Qd8
{ A very good move, the queen on d8 is very well placed because it keeps an eye on both the d4-pawn and the a5-rook. Black also intends ...Nd7 at some point possibly after the preparatory ...Rc7, to be able to recapture with the rook on d7 and add pressure on d4.   19...Qc3?!  is not precise here.  20.Qxc3  Rxc3  21.f3  . }
20. Qb4 Rc7 21. f3 Nd7
{ We challenge the knight on e5 and even if White does not trade, our knight will find better opportunities on the queenside now that f2-f3 has been played. Black is doing very well here. }
