14... Bxe6 15. Bxe6 Qxd2 16. Bxf7+ Rxf7 17. Nxd2 Rd8 18. Nf3
{ 18.Rfd1?  Rfd7-+  . } 18... Nxe4
{ It is White who needs to be careful here. This position is objectively around equal but the reason I would prefer Black is that I see more potential for a black advantage in case of even small inaccuracies.  For example, Black already dominates the d-file and he can start advancing the queenside pawns with ...b6-b5-b4 and ...a7-a5. If the construction with a black knight on c3 and a pawn on b4 would happen, White would already start to feel some difficulties. }
