Rad1 { 14.Qf4!?  is another way to reach our main line  14...exd5  15.Rad1  . }
14... exd5 15. e5 { Is not dangerous for Black either. } 15... Be6
{ This move initiates a pretty forcing and logical sequence of moves. The main point of 15...Be6 is to solve the problem of the pin on the d-file thereby introducing the ...dxc4 threat. }
16. exf6 dxc4 17. fxg7 Kxg7
{ It might seem that our king is lacking a bit of protection but in fact, ...Qf6 will come next when it becomes clear that White doesn’t have the resources to create problems for Black’s king. }
18. Nd4 Qf6 19. Nxe6+ fxe6
{ Black has no problems here, this was played in Beliavsky-Golod, Netanya 2009. Black is up a pawn, White should be able to regain it and equalize but not more. }
*

