6... cxd4 7. exd4 { 7.Nxd5?!  Qxd5  makes little sense for White. } 7... Nxc3
{ Black has a few options here but I decided to recommend this line which is extremely sound and offers nice practical chances as well. }
8. bxc3 Qc7
{ We play against the hanging pawns. In these positions, White usually needs to rely on the dynamic factors and play aggressively most of the time.  Positionally Black is doing well as the pawns can be potentially weak, so again, trades tend to favor us but we need to be alert regarding White's attacking ideas.  Usually, the best squares for our pieces are:bishop on b7 @@StartBracket@@after ...b7-b6@@EndBracket@@,knight on d7 and eventually f6,bishop on d6 where it will exert pressure on h2 and make possible the simplifying maneuver Bd6-f4 in many lines. }
