9. Bb2 Nd7
{ Now Black has ...Ba3 ideas, which wasn't possible before due to Qa4+. } 10.
Rc1 b6 11. Bd3 Bb7 12. O-O Bd6
{ Is the most natural move and should also be very playable. Play then continues }
13. c4 O-O 14. Re1 { And now I think Black should play } 14... Rae8
{ With the typical idea of playing e6-e5, possibly after the preparatory ...h7-h6.   I don't like  14...Bxf3  so much because after  15.Qxf3  Bxh2+  16.Kh1  Bf4  17.Rcd1=∞  I think White has a good initiative for the pawn. }
15. c5
{ A direct @@StartBracket@@and typical with the hanging pawns structure@@EndBracket@@ attempt to attack. }
15... bxc5 16. dxc5 Nxc5 17. Ng5
{ The classical sacrifice  17.Bxh7+?  doesn't work here:  17...Kxh7  18.Ng5+  Kg6  19.Qg4  f5-+  and Black wins. }
17... h6
{ Now White has two ways to continue the attack but it seems that Black has enough resources to defend. }
18. Bh7+ { This is the other way but after } 18... Kh8 19. Qh5 e5 20. Bf5 Re7
{ Black defends. } *

