{ This is by far the main continuation and as we have seen, the alternatives are not very challenging for Black.   6.Be2?!  dxc4  7.Bxc4  transposes to the variation @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/1p3ppp/p3pn2/2pp4/2PP4/2N1PN2/PP3PPP/R1BQKB1R w KQkq - 0 6@@EndFEN@@  6.Bd3?!  dxc4  7.Bxc4  . }
6... exd5 7. dxc5
{ This in combination with cxd5 makes little sense for White.  In general, White should take only once in the center in order to have a shot at an advantage. So either cxd5 and then keep the tension or dxc5 and keep the tension.  The combination of both trades one right after the other leads almost invariably to a very easy game for Black. }
7... Bxc5
{ Now we get a position from our main line where Black is essentially a whole tempo up. }
*

