9... Bd6 10. Nf3 O-O 11. Be2 { The most logical, preparing castles. } 11... Nd7
12. Be3 f5 13. exf5
{ 13.O-O  Nf6  14.exf5  transposes to 13.exf5 @@StartBracket@@the text move@@EndBracket@@. }
13... Nf6 14. O-O Bxf5
{ The pawn on d5 feels a lot weaker now that the e4 support is gone.  Again I like Black's chances in this position, although objectively, it is probably balanced.  Just a couple of lines to illustrate: }
15. Nd2 Be7 16. Qb3 { 16.Nc4  Qxd5⩱  . } 16... Kh8 17. Qxb7 Nxd5 18. Nc4 Be6
{ Black is ready to take on e3 or play ...Qc8 and is at least not worse in this position because the piece activity by far compensates the isolated pawn on e5. }
