h4
{ The only thing that makes sense from White's perspective.   12.Bxf8  Bxf8↑  And Black's initiative more than compensates the exchange. }
12... cxd4 13. h5 dxc3 14. Nf3
{ White has to develop.   14.hxg6?  fxg6-+  15.Bxf8  Qd2#  . } 14... Nc6 15.
Bb5 e5 16. Qg3 Qe6 17. Bxf8
{ 17.hxg6  Qxg6!  is also better for Black, just like the main line with 17.Bxf8. }
17... Bxf8 18. hxg6 Qxg6
{ This is important as otherwise, White will have a winning attack, but now White has nothing better than going for a worse endgame. }
19. Qxg6+ { 19.Qh4?  Be7-+  . } 19... hxg6 20. Bxc6 bxc6 21. Nxe5 a5
{ Black is much better in this endgame due to his strong bishop pair and passed pawns on the queenside. }
