{ This has been tried a few times but the knight on e2 stands worse than on f3 @@StartBracket@@unlike the Grunfeld, here White does not need to worry about Bg4@@EndBracket@@ so Black gets a nice game by simple means.   9.Nf3  Transposes to our main line with 8.Nf3 O-O 9.Bc4. }
9... Nc6 10. O-O b6
{ This seems the most harmonious way of developing our forces here. We are planning ...Bb7, ...Rc8 and then something like ...cxd4, ...Na5 and ...Nc4 with clear counterplay on the queenside.  Again, this type of play resembles the Grunfeld and having e6 and Be7 here instead of g6, Bg7 in a way feels even more sound for Black. }
