14. Qg3 Rd8 15. Rd1
{ 15.Bh6  g6  16.Rfd1  Qxa2  transposes to the variation  @@StartFEN@@r1br2k1/pp2bppp/4p3/3qP3/8/3B2Q1/P4PPP/1RB2RK1 w - - 3 15@@EndFEN@@  15.Rd1  Qxa2  16.Bh6  g6  . }
15... Qxa2 16. Bxh7+
{ Is a very forcing line that leads to a draw.   16.Bg5  Bxg5  17.Qxg5  Bd7  Allows Black to easily complete his development. Black is better here. }
16... Kxh7 17. Rxd8 Bxd8 18. Qd3+ g6 19. Qxd8 Qxb1
{ Now the white bishop is pinned so White has nothing better than perpetual check. }
20. Qh4+ Kg8 21. Qd8+ Kh7 { With a draw. } *

