13... cxd4
{ Now we ignore Rxg7. It turns out it gives White no more than a draw, although it's quite complicated. Let's take a look at the lines.   I don't quite like the move  13...Rg8  In this specific move order, White has the option of playing  14.Qf4  Bb7  15.Bd3  Now f7 is under attack and although this position is still complicated, I like White's chances.   That's the reason why I prefer  13...cxd4  . }
14. cxd4 Bb7
{ This is the last chance for White to go for Rxg7 as otherwise, Black plays ...Rc8 and there is always ...Rxc1 in case of Rxg7. }
