9... O-O 10. Re1 Nc6 11. Be4 Nce7
{ A typical move, strengthening the control over d5. Now it only remains to develop the bishop @@StartBracket@@...Bd7-c6@@EndBracket@@ and Black will have a very nice position.  White has to try and play active but I don't see how he can create problems for Black here. }
12. Bg5 Qd6 13. Qd2 Bd7 14. Ne5 Nxc3 15. Qxc3 Nd5 16. Qb3 Bc6
{ Black is doing well. The position is more or less balanced.   We should not be afraid of the trade on c6 as after  17.Nxc6  bxc6  leads to a typically good position for Black where the pawn on d4 tends to be weaker than its black counterpart on c6. }
