{ We basically get one of the main lines but with the extra move ...h6, which is actually pretty good for Black.  In many of these lines, White uses the attack on h7 as a way to gain tempo @@StartBracket@@Bd3 and Qc2@@EndBracket@@, which now simply doesn't happen.  Also, it's hard to carry out the g2-g4 push with the center open plus the pawn on h6 prevents Bg5 or Ng5 ideas. }
